main event: Several observers at Cannon AFB, New Mexico spotted a round, orange/yellow object that maneuvered in the sky for over 30 minutes on May 4, 1964.
interesting points: The object was first observed at 45 degrees elevation and 270 degrees azimuth, and it flew in a straight line parallel to the horizon.
The object maneuvered by 'twinkling' for about 5 minutes.
There were a total of 4 sightings of the object about 30 minutes apart, also seen at Clovis, New Mexico.
The object's elevation ranged from 45 to 33 degrees, and it was reported to be flying east.
The object was initially thought to be an aircraft on final approach, but no aircraft were detected in the area.
witnesses: multiple observers at Cannon AFB and Clovis, New Mexico
